criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  Clinically definite diagnosis of MS;

          -  Age 18 to 60;

          -  Capable of understanding and complying with the study protocol;

          -  Able to read and write in English;

          -  Visual acuity of at least 20/70 with correction in order to work on the computer
             screen;

          -  Stable disease at the time of entry into the study (relapse free for at least 90
             days);

          -  Subjective concerns about their cognitive functioning (based on the Perceived Deficits
             Questionnaire); and

          -  Home internet access;

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Other medical causes of dementia or other neurological disorders that may impact
             cognition or emotions;

          -  Evidence of major psychiatric disorder; or

          -  Major functional limitations that preclude them from participating in the study.
